4. $MELI

MercadoLibre is arguably the most dominant e-commerce and fintech platform in Latin America, its moat is an entire ecosystem competitors simply cannot replicate.

MELI reached 76.8M unique active buyers (+26% YoY), its highest since Q1 2021. It continues to expand aggressively in Colombia, Chile, Ecuador, and Peru, markets where e-commerce penetration is still in early stages.

Mercado Pago is the PayPal + Venmo + Square + Chime + Stripe of Latin America, all in one.

Its credit portfolio is up 100% YoY while maintaining record-low defaults. It is now the #2 financial institution in Mexico by active users and #1 in app downloads.

Latin America is notoriously difficult to operate in, logistics, inflation, infrastructure gaps. MELI solved these challenges over 20 years. Even Amazon has struggled to replicate its model in Brazil and Mexico.

By 2030, the companyâ€™s revenue is projected to grow from $550M to $1.65B, with continued expansion into payments, logistics, and credit.
